  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The address, \"My brethren and my people,\" is expressive of condescending goodwill; cf. on אחי,   ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 30:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 19:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". What David here says (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:3-7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") of the temple building, he had in substance already (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:7-13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") said to his son Solomon: I, it was with my heart, i.e., I purposed (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") to build a house of rest for the ark of the covenant of Jahve, and the footstool of the feet of our God, i.e., for the ark and for the capporeth upon it, which is called \"footstool of the feet of our God,\" because God was enthroned above the cherubim upon the capporeth. \"And I have prepared to build,\" i.e., prepared labour and materials, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:2-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". - In ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " David states how his election to be king was of God, who had chosen Judah to be ruler (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 5:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); and just so (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") had God chosen Solomon from among all his many sons to be heir to the throne, and committed to him the building of the temple; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The expression, \"throne of the kingdom of Jahve,\" and more briefly, \"throne of Jahve\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 29:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", or מלכוּתי, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 17:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), denotes that Jahve is the true King of Israel, and had chosen Solomon as He had chosen David to be holder and administrator of His kingdom dominion. - On ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 22:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 17:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; and with the condition וגו יחזק אם, cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 3:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 9:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where God imposes an exactly similar condition on Solomon. הזּה כּיּום, as is done at this time; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 8:61",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and the commentary on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 2:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On this speech J. H. Mich. well remarks: \"tota haec narratio aptata est ad prospositum Davidis: vult enim Salomoni auctoritatem apud principes et fratres conciliare, ostendendo, non humana, sed divina voluntate electum esse,\" To this David adds an exhortation to the whole assembly (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), and to his son Solomon (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), to hold fast their faithfulness to God.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
]